=C2=A0

Capitol Hill might be nearing a lull between the confirmation storms and th=
e increasingly heated spending negotiations ahead of the March 14 governmen=
t shutdown deadline. (Of course, with Musk and Trump running things, you ca=
n never count on a lull.) Yes, we hear shutdown threats all the time, and t=
he House, Senate, and president almost
always sort things out at the 11th hour. But this time, Democrats are doing=
 everything they can to telegraph that they will not save a Republican spen=
ding bill unless Trump and Musk relent from their attempts to override Cong=
